# The year, month and maturity.stage variables were coded as integers in the original data set. 
# Here we would like to code them as factors. Create a new variable for each of these variables in the squid data frame and re code them as factors. 

# convert variables to factors
squid$Fmaturity <- factor(squid$maturity.stage)
squid$Fmonth <- factor(squid$month)
squid$Fyear <- factor(squid$year)

#Basic programming in R

#area of circle
#the equation
circle.area <- function(d)
  {
    pi * (d/2)^2
}
circle.area(10)
## [1] 78.53982
#test on a vector of diameters, which ranges from 0 to 50 
cir.diam <- seq(from = 0, to = 50, by = 10
                )

#test the function
circle.area(cir.diam)
## [1]    0.00000   78.53982  314.15927  706.85835 1256.63706 1963.49541
